    <abstract>
      <t>Routing information reduction by BGP Route Reflection or Confederation can result in persistent internal BGP route oscillations with certain routing setups and network topologies.  This document specifies two sets of additional paths that can be used to eliminate these route oscillations in a network.
	 </t>
